        "last_activity_date": 1359843514,
        "creation_date": 1359763629,
        "answer_count": 4,
        "title": "Random Normal Distribution in Java returns values outside range",
        "body": "<blockquote>\n  <p><strong>Possible Duplicate:<\/strong><br>\n  <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/629798/problem-with-random-nextgaussian\">problem with Random.nextGaussian()<\/a>  <\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n\n\n\n<p>I am working to develop small java application to make random normal distribution and give 50 values.  I use mean = 0.0 and std = 1.0, but the problem I got results out of the bounds there is some values less than 0.0 and else more than 1.0 , can anyone help me?<\/p>\n\n<p>The following is the code that I used:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>public static void main(String[] args) {\n\n    double[] list = new double[50];\n    double mean = 0.0, std = 1.0;\n    Random rng = new Random();\n\n            // to generate 50 values random normal distribution\n    for(int i = 0;i&lt;list.length;i++) {\n      list[i] = mean + std * rng.nextGaussian();\n    }\n\n            // to print the generated values from the list\n    for(int i = 0;i&lt;list.length;i++) \n            {\n            System.out.println(list[i]); \n    }\n\n\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
